On Sun, 21 Apr 2002, Courtney Hook wrote:

> The lights on the floor for the drive selector aren't working, and I cannot
> find a schematic anywhere as to how to trace them back. I have a grey wire
> with a red stripe hanging by the fuse panel, but am afraid to hook it up to
> power in case I fry something. My thought however is that it may be the wire
> that is for the lighting on the floor selector (you know, 1,2, D, R, P) :-)
> Does anyone have a schematic or could trace theirs? The bulbs seem fine but
> no lights at night.

exploded drawing is on page 43 of the Auto tranny section of Bentley, the
power for the selector light is from the instrument cluster lighting if I
recall. the wiring diagram is the supplement A on page 42 of the Bentley
wiring section, goes to fuse #1 

